photo.description: Victory Over the North, executed by Astyanax-Scaevola Bosio, adorns the interior northwest pillar of Arc de Triomphe de l'Étoile. Seated at the centre, ictory holds a tablet on which she has inscribed: "Austerlitz/Iéna/Friedland and Ulm/Wagram and Eylau." Positioned at her right and left, four genies shoulder long garlands whose ends pill over with fruit. The Arc de Triomphe stands in the centre of the Place Charles de Gaulle, also known as the Place de l'Étoile (Star Square). Designed by Jean Chalgrin between 1806 and 1836, the 51 meter high, 45-meter wide monument is the second largest triumphal arch in existence. It honors those who fought for France, particularly during the Napoleonic Wars.
